  "prompt": "Did anyone find House of Cards boring?",
  "response": "Yes, while \"House of Cards\" garnered significant praise for its gripping storytelling, strong performances (particularly by Kevin Spacey and Robin Wright), and its incisive portrayal of political maneuvering, not all viewers found it engaging. Some critics and audience members felt that certain seasons became repetitive or that the pacing slowed down, making the series seem less compelling. Additionally, controversies surrounding cast members and shifts in narrative focus in later seasons may have contributed to some viewers losing interest. As with any long-running show, opinions varied, and while many appreciated its depth and complexity, others found it less engaging over time.",
